==English==

===Etymology===
Italian [[maneggiare]] "to handle, manage" < Vulgar Latin ''*manidiare'' "to handle", derived from Latin [[manus]] "hand" < Proto-Indo-European '''*men-''' "hand, to take in one's hand". It is cognate with French [[manier]] and Spanish [[manejar]].

